 i.e 180% total interest) - 1 + (180% of 1) => 1 + 1.8 => 2.8 The user can claim the zCLAY Bonds for equivalent value of CLAY after the maturation date. The user has to lock his CLAY in to zCLAY bonds for atleast 3 years. They are open to trade these bonds on a secondary market (i.e. via LP pools on Sumero)","version":1}},"settings":{"compilationTarget":{"contracts/ClayBonds.sol":"ClayBonds"},"evmVersion":"istanbul","libraries":{},"metadata":{"bytecodeHash":"ipfs","useLiteralContent":true},"optimizer":{"enabled":true,"runs":1000},"remappings":[]},"sources":{"@openzeppelin/contracts/math/SafeMath.sol":{"content":"// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT

